# Backend Testing Rules (Extension)

These rules extend the core testing philosophy with backend-specific practices.

---

## 1. Stub Rules
- Stubs must implement domain or application interfaces
- Must be deterministic
- Must contain no business logic

---

## 2. Stub Placement
- Stubs belong in the Infrastructure layer (test-only implementations)

---

## 3. Naming Convention
- `InMemoryXRepository` for persistence stubs
- `FakeXService` for service stubs

---

## 4. Backend Testing Focus
- Prioritize correctness of domain and application layers
- Prefer integration tests to validate interaction between layers